com.ziesemer.utils.pacProxySelector
Class PacProxySelector

java.lang.Object
  java.net.ProxySelector
      com.ziesemer.utils.pacProxySelector.PacProxySelector

public class PacProxySelector
extends ProxySelector

A ProxySelector implementation that supports proxy auto-config (PAC) files, as summarized at http://en.wikipedia.org./wiki/Proxy_auto-config. (Look for the links to the archived Netscape documentation.)

Author:
Mark A. Ziesemer <www.ziesemer.com>

main

public static void main(String[] args)
                 throws Exception

Can be used as a wrapper for another program's main method.

It first calls setDefaultFromProperties(). It then assumes that the first argument is the name of another class containing a main(String[] args) method, which is then called with any remaining arguments.

configureFromProperties

public static ProxySelector configureFromProperties()
                                             throws Exception

Returns a new ProxySelector instance. Checks System.getProperty(String) then System.getenv() for a value named PAC_LOCATION_PROPERTY.

If found, a new PacProxySelector is returned using the value as the location of the PAC script. Values must be a valid input to URL.URL(String). Files from the local file system may be supported using file:// URLs.

Otherwise, the current selector is returned from ProxySelector.getDefault().

Throws:
Exception
